<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1885-03-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1885-03-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="56" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d56">
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">No. 56.</seg></opener>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Hall</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-03-16"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 16,
                            1885</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Hall is instructed to make known to the Government of Guatemala that it
                        will be held strictly responsible for any injuries to the telegraphic
                        cables, property, or interests of American citizens in Central America
                        committed with its connivance or under its authority.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>